    <text type="correspondence">
        <body>
            <div1>
                <pb facs="ccda.corr000210.001.jpg"/>

                <fw type="letterhead" place="top-left" hand="#h01">CHAS. W. CHESNUTT<lb/>1005
                    WILLIAMSON BUILDING<lb/>CLEVELAND, O.</fw>


                <dateline>Cleveland, <date when="1903-07-03">July 3, 1903.</date></dateline>

                <opener> <address>
                    <addrLine> Horace Traubel, Esq.,</addrLine>
                    <addrLine>Camden, N.J.</addrLine>
                    </address> <salute>My dear Traubel:<ref type="editorial" resp="#slg" n="1"
                    target="Traub"/></salute> </opener>

                <p hand="#h02">Thank you very much for your kindly characterization of my work in
                    The Conservator <ref type="editorial" resp="#slg" n="2" target="Conserv"/> in
                    June. Appreciation of this sort is very encouraging. If present tendencies
                    continue much longer, the colored people of this nation are likely to need
                    friends and it is quite clear that they can count you among them.</p>

                <closer> <salute>Cordially yours,</salute> <signed hand="#h03">Chas. W.
                    Chesnutt</signed> </closer>


            </div1>

        </body>

    </text>

